    "what_description": "Matricaria transcaucasica is an annual or biennial herbaceous plant belonging to the family Asteraceae. Its stems are slender, erect, and 20-70 cm tall, bearing linear to lanceolate leaves that are 5-15 cm long. The plant produces yellow, daisy-like flower heads with 5-20 capitula and 15-30 florets, each 5-7 mm in diameter. The florets are tubular and ligulate, with the ligulate flowers 4-5 mm long and the tubular flowers 1-2 mm long. The plant's achenes are 1-2 mm long and crowned with a ring of 5-7 scales.",
