    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Matricaria transcaucasica are flavonoids and phenolic acids, which include apigenin, luteolin, quercetin, kaempferol and chlorogenic acid. These compounds are responsible for the plant's antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, with apigenin and luteolin exhibiting significant inhibitory activity against enzymes involved in the inflammatory response and kaempferol and quercetin showing strong free radical scavenging activity. Chlorogenic acid, a key phenolic acid constituent of the plant, has been found to have a protective effect against oxidative stress and inflammation in various tissues. The flavonoids and phenolic acids in Matricaria transcaucasica may contribute to its reported therapeutic effects, including its use in traditional medicine for treating various conditions such as gastrointestinal disorders and respiratory infections. The antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties of these constituents suggest their potential as natural therapeutic agents for the prevention and treatment of chronic diseases.",
