    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Matricaria transcaucasica are tincture, made by extracting the plant's bioactive compounds with a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, infusion, which involves steeping the dried flowers in hot water to release their active ingredients, tea, a more concentrated form of infusion, and salve, a topical application of the plant's extract in a carrier oil to treat skin conditions. Matricaria transcaucasica essential oil, obtained through steam distillation, is used in aromatherapy to promote relaxation and reduce stress. These preparations are used to treat various health issues, including insomnia, anxiety, and skin problems, due to the plant's content of flavonoids, coumarins, and terpenes, which have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. The essential oil and tincture are also used to treat wounds and promote tissue repair, while the infusion and tea are consumed to support digestive health and alleviate symptoms of menopausal hot flashes. The salve is applied topically to soothe skin irritations and promote wound healing.",
